paragraph: Harry suddenly remembers that he read the name Nicolas on a chocolate frog card , which reminds Hermione that she had seen the name in a book she picked up from the library , and the team discover that he was a famous alchemist who is the only known maker of the Philosopher 's Stone , whose powers include turning any metal to gold and producing the Elixir of Life , a potion that can make the drinker immortal.The Gryffindor versus Hufflepuff match arrives and Severus , who referees the match , is predictably biassed , while on the stands Ronald and Neville get into a scuffle with Malfoy , Vincent , and Gregory after Malfoy made some rude comments towards the players of their house 's team as well as both of them .
